{"kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Build a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/AppFeedbackCore\/documentation\/AppFeedbackCore\/FeedbackClient"},{"type":"text","text":", submit a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/AppFeedbackCore\/documentation\/AppFeedbackCore\/FeedbackReport"},{"type":"text","text":", and the SDK does the rest."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"Overview","level":2,"text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"AppFeedbackCore","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is designed to drop into any Apple-platform app with three lines of setup and one async call to submit. There are no global singletons, no compile-time configuration steps, and no UI dependencies.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Step 1 — Add the package","level":2,"anchor":"Step-1-Add-the-package"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In your "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Package.swift"},{"type":"text","text":":"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":[".package(path: \"..\/AppFeedbackSDK\"),","\/\/ or, when published:","\/\/ .package(url: \"https:\/\/github.com\/hayek\/AppFeedbackSDK\", from: \"0.2.0\"),"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Link ","type":"text"},{"code":"AppFeedbackCore","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to your app target. The SwiftUI sheet lives in the separate ","type":"text"},{"code":"AppFeedbackUI","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" product — link that too if you want the drop-in form."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Step-2-Build-a-client","level":2,"text":"Step 2 — Build a client"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Construct a ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/AppFeedbackCore\/documentation\/AppFeedbackCore\/FeedbackClient","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" once at app start and hold a reference. Device info is collected lazily on every submission, so a long-lived client always reports the ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"current"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" app version even after updates.","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["import AppFeedbackCore","","@MainActor","let feedback = FeedbackClient(","    appName: \"AcmeApp\",","    transport: GitHubDirectTransport(","        owner: \"acme-co\",","        repo: \"feedback\",","        token: SecretLoader.gitHubToken","    )",")"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"appName"},{"type":"text","text":" parameter overrides the auto-detected app name (otherwise the SDK reads "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CFBundleDisplayName"},{"type":"text","text":" \/ "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CFBundleName"},{"type":"text","text":" from your bundle)."}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Step-3-Submit-a-report","level":2,"text":"Step 3 — Submit a report"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["do {","    let issueNumber = try await feedback.submit(","        FeedbackReport(","            type: .bug,","            title: \"Crash on launch\",","            description: \"Happens immediately after sign-in.\",","            contactEmail: \"user@example.com\"","        )","    )","    print(\"Filed issue #\\(issueNumber)\")","} catch {","    \/\/ See ``FeedbackSubmissionError`` for the error cases the GitHub transport throws.","    print(\"Failed: \\(error)\")","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"That’s it. The transport renders the body, applies labels, calls GitHub, and returns the issue number."}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Step 4 — Inject device info (optional)","level":2,"anchor":"Step-4-Inject-device-info-optional"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If you want to override what ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/AppFeedbackCore\/documentation\/AppFeedbackCore\/DeviceInfo\/current(appName:)"},{"type":"text","text":" collects — for example, to distinguish iPad from iPhone or to inject test data — build a "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/AppFeedbackCore\/documentation\/AppFeedbackCore\/DeviceInfo","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" directly and pass it to the alternate "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/AppFeedbackCore\/documentation\/AppFeedbackCore\/FeedbackClient\/init(transport:deviceInfo:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" initializer:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let device = DeviceInfo(","    appName: \"AcmeApp\",","    appVersion: \"1.2.3\",","    buildNumber: \"456\",","    model: \"iPad14,1\",","    osName: \"iPadOS\",","    osVersion: \"Version 18.2 (Build 22C150)\"",")","let feedback = FeedbackClient(transport: transport, deviceInfo: device)"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"With this initializer the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"deviceInfo"},{"type":"text","text":" value is frozen for the lifetime of the client. Use it for tests, screenshots, or when you need full control of the metadata column."}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Next steps","level":2,"anchor":"Next-steps"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/AppFeedbackCore\/documentation\/AppFeedbackCore\/BodyFormat","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" — see exactly what gets written to the GitHub issue body.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/AppFeedbackCore\/documentation\/AppFeedbackCore\/CustomTransports","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" — replace ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/AppFeedbackCore\/documentation\/AppFeedbackCore\/GitHubDirectTransport","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" with a server-side relay.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/AppFeedbackCore\/docume